 MATE 18.10 Will Drop 32-Bit Support for New Installations], '''Softpedia News'''</ref><ref>[https://distrowatch.com/weekly.php?issue=20181022#ubuntumate DistroWatch Weekly, Issue 786, 22 October 2018]</ref>\n| ''Cosmic Cuttlefish''\n| 2018-10-18\n| July 2019\n| Previous non-LTS 64-bit-only release, end of 32-bit support. Features MATE 1.20.<ref>[https://ubuntu-mate.org/blog/ubuntu-mate-cosmic-beta/ Ubuntu MATE 18.10 Beta | Ubuntu MATE]</ref><ref>[https://ubuntu-mate.org/blog/ubuntu-mate-cosmic-final-release/ Ubuntu MATE 18.10 Final Release | Ubuntu MATE]</ref><ref>[https://www.omgubuntu.co.uk/2018/10/ubuntu-mate-18-10-gpd-pocket-laptop Ubuntu MATE 18.10 is Now Available for the GPD Pocket Laptop - OMG! Ubuntu!]</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap; background:gold;\"|19.04\n| ''Disco Dingo''\n| 2019-04-18\n| January 2020\n| Previous non-LTS 64-bit-only release. Features MATE 1.20 and NVIDIA Drivers.<ref>https://ubuntu-mate.org/blog/ubuntu-mate-disco-final-release/</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap; background:#a0e75a;\"|19.10\n| ''Eoan Ermine''\n| 2019-10-17\n| July 2020\n| Current non-LTS 64-bit-only release. Features MATE 1.22.2 and replaces VLC with GNOME MPV as default media player.<ref>https://ubuntu-mate.org/blog/ubuntu-mate-19-10-eoan-ermine-release/</ref>\n|}\n\n== Reception ==\nIn a May 2016 review Jesse Smith of [[DistroWatch]] concluded, \"despite my initial problems getting Ubuntu MATE installed and running smoothly, I came away with a positive view of the distribution. The project is providing a very friendly desktop experience that requires few hardware resources by modern standards. I also want to tip my hat to the default theme used on Ubuntu MATE.\"<ref>{{cite web|url = http://distrowatch.com/weekly.php?issue=20160509#ubuntumate|title = Ubuntu MATE 16.04 LTS|accessdate = 13 May 2016|last = Smith|first = Jesse|work=[[DistroWatch]]|date = 9 May 2016}}</ref>\n\nAs of August 2017, Ubuntu MATE ranked at 24 on the [[DistroWatch|Distrowatch]] 6 month page hit ranking.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://distrowatch.com/|title=DistroWatch.com: Put the fun back into computing. Use Linux, BSD.|date=2017-08-06|access-date=2017-08-07|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170806193337/http://distrowatch.com/|archive-date=2017-08-06}}</ref>\n\nDedoimedo reviewed Ubuntu MATE in July 2018, and wrote that \"[offers] a wealth of visual and functional changes ... You really have the ability to implement anything and everything, and all of it natively, from within the system's interface.\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dedoimedo.com/computers/ubuntu-mate-pimp.html|title=Ubuntu MATE - Pimp your desktop to perfection|website=www.dedoimedo.com|language=en|access-date=2018-08-27}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Comparison of Linux distributions]]\n* [[GTK+]]\n* [[Linux Mint]]\n* [[MATE (software)|MATE]]\n* [[Ubuntu GNOME]]\n* [[Ubuntu (operating system)|Ubuntu Unity]]\n* [[Xubuntu]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commonscat|Ubuntu MATE}}\n* {{Official website|https://ubuntu-mate.org/}}\n* {{DistroWatch|ubuntumate|NAME=Ubuntu MATE}}\n* [https://ubuntu-mate.community/wiki Official Wiki]\n\n{{Ubuntu}}\n{{Linux distributions}}\n{{FOSS}}\n{{Portal bar|Linux|Free and open-source software}}\n\n[[Category:IA-32 Linux distributions]]\n[[Category:Linux distributions]]\n[[Category:Operating system distributions bootable from read-only media]]\n[[Category:Ubuntu derivatives]]\n[[Category:X86-64 Linux distributions]]\n", "name_user": "71.10.36.253", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eReleases)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ubuntu_MATE"}
{"title_page": "Hotel Transylvania (franchise)", "text_new": "{{DISPLAYTITLE: ''Hotel Transylvania'' (franchise)}}\n{{Infobox media franchise\n| title         = ''Hotel Transylvania''\n| image         = Hotel Transylvania logo.svg\n| creator       = [[Todd Durham]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.visualhollywood.com/movies_2012/hotel_transylvania/notes.pdf|title=Columbia Pictures Press Kit - Hotel Transylvania|access-date=2017-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121222034223/http://www.visualhollywood.com/movies_2012/hotel_transylvania/notes.pdf|archive-date=2012-12-22|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| owner = [[Sony Pictures Animation]]\n| films         = {{Plainlist|\n* ''[[Hotel Transylvania]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[Hotel Transylvania 2]]'' (2015)\n* ''[[Hotel Transylvania 3: Summer Vacation]]'' (2018)\n* ''Hotel Transylvania 4'' (2021)\n}}\n| novels     = {{plainlist|\n* ''Kakieland Katastrophe''\n* ''My Little Monster-Sitter''\n* ''Motel Transylvania''\n}}\n| shorts     = {{plainlist|\n* ''[[#Goodnight Mr. Foot|Goodnight Mr. Foot]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[#Puppy!|Puppy!]]'' (2017)\n}}\n| tv     =\n''[[Hotel Transylvania: The Series]]'' (2017\u2013present)\n| plays         =\n| vgs           = {{unbulleted list|''[[#Video games|Hotel Transylvania Social Game]]''|''[[#Video games|Hotel Transylvania]]''|''[[#Video games|Hotel Transylvania Dash]]''|''[[#Video games|Hotel Transylvania BooClips Deluxe App]]''|''[[#Video games|Hotel Transylvania 3: Monsters Overboard]]''}}\n| soundtracks = {{unbulleted list|''[[Hotel Transylvania#Soundtrack|Hotel Transylvania]]''|''[[Hotel Transylvania 2#Music|Hotel Transylvania 2]]''|''[[Hotel Transylvania 3: Summer Vacation#Music|Hotel Transylvania 3: Summer Vacation]]''}}\n}}\n'''''Hotel Transylvania''''' is an American [[media franchise]] created by comedy writer [[Todd Durham]]. It consists of three theatrical films, three graphic novels and two short films produced by [[Sony Pictures Animation]], as well as a TV series broadcast on [[Disney Channel]] and several video games. The series consists of an [[ensemble cast]], usually led by the voices of  [[Adam Sandler]], [[Andy Samberg]] and [[Selena Gomez]].\n\nThe first film, ''[[Hotel Transylvania]]'', was released in September 2012, a sequel, ''[[Hotel Transylvania 2]]'', was released in September 2015 and a third film, ''[[Hotel Transylvania 3: Summer Vacation]]'', was released in July 2018. The films have received mixed reviews from critics and grossed over $1.3 billion worldwide against a combined production budget of $245 million. A fourth installment tentatively called ''Hotel Transylvania 4'' was announced in February 2019 to be in development, and is set to be released on December 22, 2021.<ref name=HT4>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/hotel-transylvania-4-to-hit-theaters-in-december-2021-1203150290/|title=\u2018Hotel Transylvania 4\u2019 to Hit Theaters in December 2021|last=Donnelly|first=Matt|last2=Donnelly|first2=Matt|date=2019-02-26|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-02-27}}</ref>\n\n==Origin==\nComedy writer [[Todd Durham]] conceived and created a [[Bible (screenwriting)|bible]] for a [[multimedia franchise]] called ''Hotel Transylvania'', consisting of several films, television series, video games, toys, books, merchandising, hotel chain, and theme park.  After authoring the book of the same name, he took the package unsolicited to Columbia Pictures and set it up at Sony Pictures Animation where he became the first screenwriter on the project.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.visualhollywood.com/movies_2012/hotel_transylvania/notes.pdf|title=Production Notes - Hotel Transylvania|access-date=2017-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121222034223/http://www.visualhollywood.com/movies_2012/hotel_transylvania/notes.pdf|archive-date=2012-12-22|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sonypicturesanimation.com/pastfilms.php?s=hotelt|title=Sony Pictures Animation - Hotel Transylvania}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/HotelT/|title=Official Website - Hotel Transylvania}}</ref>\n\n==Feature films==\n{{Infobox film\n| name        = Hotel Transylvania (film series)\n| image       =\n| caption     =\n| director    = [[Genndy Tartakovsky]]\n| producer    = Michelle Murdocca\n| writer      = {{ubl|[[Peter Baynham]] ''(1)''|[[Robert Smigel]] (''1 & 2'')|[[Adam Sandler]] (''2'')|Genndy Tartakovsky (''3'')|[[Michael McCullers]] (''3'')}}\n| starring    = {{ubl|Adam Sandler|[[Andy Samberg]]|[[Selena Gomez]]}}\n| music       = [[Mark Mothersbaugh]]\n| based on    = {{Based on|Characters|[[Todd Durham]]}}\n| distributor = [[Sony Pictures Releasing]]\n| released    = 2012\u2013present\n| budget      = $245 million '''(3 films)'''\n| gross       = $1.361 billion '''(3 films)'''\n}}\n\n===''Hotel Transylvania'' (2012)===\n{{Main|Hotel Transylvania}}\n''[[Hotel Transylvania]]'' was released on September 28, 2012, and is about a human named Jonathan ([[Andy Samberg]]), who unwittingly stumbles upon the hotel and instantly falls in love with Dracula's teenage daughter, Mavis ([[Selena Gomez]]), and eventually dates, despite Dracula's ([[Adam Sandler]]) attempts to keep Jonathan away from his daughter.\n\n===''Hotel Transylvania 2'' (2015)===\n{{Main|Hotel Transylvania 2}}\n''[[Hotel Transylvania 2]]'' was released on September 25, 2015, and is about Mavis and Johnny, who have a half-human/half-vampire son named Dennis. Mavis thinks Hotel Transylvania isn't the right place to raise Dennis and wants to raise him in California. When Dracula is disappointed that Dennis does not have any vampire abilities, he helps his friends make his grandson a vampire.\n\n===''Hotel Transylvania 3: Summer Vacation'' (2018)===\n{{Main|Hotel Transylvania 3: Summer Vacation}}\nIn November 2015, Sony Pictures Animation announced that ''[[Hotel Transylvania 3: Summer Vacation|Hotel Transylvania 3]]'' would be released on September 21, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lesnick|first1=Silas|title=Hotel Transylvania 3 Opens Its Doors in 2018!|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/628529-hotel-transylvania-3-2018#/slide/1|publisher=ComingSoon.net|accessdate=November 3, 2015|date=November 2, 2015}}</ref> This was later resolved during early 2017 when the new release date was pushed forward to July 13, 2018. Despite previously leaving the series to develop other projects, Genndy Tartakovsky returned as director for this installment.<ref>{{cite web|author=Amid Amidi |url=http://www.cartoonbrew.com/feature-film/genndy-tartakovsky-isnt-done-hotel-transylvania-will-direct-third-film-franchise-140820.html |title=Genndy Tartakovsky Isn\u2019t Done With \u2018Hotel Transylvania,\u2019 Will Direct Third Film in Franchise |publisher=Cartoonbrew.com |date=June 20, 2016|accessdate=June 20, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Roberts|first1=Sheila|title=20 Things to Know About \u2018Hotel Transylvania 2\u2032|url=http://collider.com/hotel-transylvania-2-20-things-to-know-about-the-sequel/|publisher=Collider.com|accessdate=November 3, 2015|date=September 25, 2015}}</ref> The third film is about Dracula unwittingly falling for Ericka, a descendant of monster hunter [[Abraham Van Helsing|Van Helsing]], while on a cruise ship with his family.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Moore|first1=Debi|title=Synopsis and More Details on Hotel Transylvania 3 - Dread Central|url=https://www.dreadcentral.com/news/207350/synopsis-details-hotel-transylvania-3/|accessdate=19 January 2017|work=Dread Central|date=18 January 2017}}</ref> It is the first film in the series not to be released in September, as well as the first one not to feature the hotel as its main setting.\n\n===''Hotel Transylvania 4'' (2021)===\nOn February 26, 2019, Sony Pictures Animation announced that a fourth film will be released on December 22, 2021.<ref name=\"HT4\" />\n\n==Television series==\n{{Main|Hotel Transylvania: The Series}}\nA television series based on the film premiered on June 25, 2017.<ref name=VarietyHotelTV /> Developed and produced by [[Nelvana Limited]], in partnership with Sony Pictures Animation, the prequel series focuses on the teenage years of Mavis and her friends at the Hotel Transylvania.<ref name=VarietyHotelTV>{{cite news|last1=Steinberg|first1=Brian|title=Nelvana, Sony Pictures Animation Ready \u2018Hotel Transylvania\u2019 For TV|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/nelvana-sony-pictures-animation-hotel-transylvania-tv-1201539674/|accessdate=November 3, 2015|work=Variety|date=July 14, 2015}}</ref> [[Sony Pictures Television]] handles distribution in the United States, while Nelvana distributes the series outside the United States.<ref name=VarietyHotelTV /> It is airing on the [[Disney Channel]] worldwide.<ref name=\"DeadlineHT3EmojiGhost\">{{cite web|last1=Pederson|first1=Erik|title=Sony Animation Dates \u2018Hotel Transylvania 3\u2019, \u2018Emojimovie\u2019 & More; \u2018Ghostbusters\u2019 TV Series Set|url=http://deadline.com/2016/06/hotel-transylvania-3-emoji-movie-ghostbusters-sony-animation-1201775965/|publisher=Deadline|accessdate=June 21, 2016|date=June 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Short films==\n===''Goodnight Mr. Foot''===\n''Goodnight Mr. Foot'' is a traditionally animated short film based on ''Hotel Transylvania'', featuring Bigfoot from the film. Premiering in time for Halloween, on October 26, 2012, the short was shown exclusively in [[Regal Entertainment Group|Regal Entertainment Group Cinemas]], before the theatrical shows of ''Hotel Transylvania''. As [[Sony Pictures Animation]]'s first traditionally animated film, it was written and directed by [[Genndy Tartakovsky]] himself, who also animated the short with the help of [[Rough Draft Studios]]. Animated in the style of [[Bob Clampett]], [[Tex Avery]] and [[Chuck Jones]],<ref name=PRNewswireGoodnight>{{cite news|title=No Trick, Big Halloween Treat from Sony Pictures Animation's HOTEL TRANSYLVANIA Director Genndy Tartakovsky|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/no-trick-big-halloween-treat-from-sony-pictures-animations-hotel-transylvania-director-genndy-tartakovsky-175869981.html|accessdate=November 3, 2015|newspaper=PR Newswire|date=October 25, 2012|author=Sony Pictures Animation}}</ref> Tartakovsky created the short in four weeks during the final production stages of the main film.<ref name=CartoonBrewGoodnight>{{cite news|last=Beck|first=Jerry|title=Sony Releases Genndy Tartakovsky\u2019s new short \"Goodnight Mr. Foot\"|url=http://www.cartoonbrew.com/animators/genndy-tartakovskys-new-short-goodnight-mr-foot-72407.html|accessdate=November 3, 2015|newspaper=[[Cartoon Brew]]|date=October 25, 2012}}</ref> Bigfoot (who had a non-speaking role in ''Hotel Transylvania'') was voiced by [[Corey Burton]] while the [[Witchcraft|Witch]] [[Maid]] was voiced by [[Rose Abdoo]]. Both voice actors provided additional voices in ''Hotel Transylvania''.<ref name=USATodayGoodnight>{{cite news|last=Alexander|first=Bryan|title=New Bigfoot sighting in 'Hotel Transylvania' short film|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2012/10/24/hotel-transylvania-goodnight-mr-foot/1649599/|accessdate=November 3, 2015|newspaper=USA Today|date=October 24, 2012}}</ref>\n\nTaking place before the events of ''Hotel Transylvania'', the short stars Bigfoot, whose rest in Hotel Transylvania is being constantly disturbed by an overly enthusiastic witch maid.<ref name=PRNewswireGoodnight />\n\n===''Puppy!''===\n''Puppy!'' is a [[computer animation|CG-animated]] [[fantasy comedy]] [[short film]] based on ''Hotel Transylvania'', featuring Dennis (voiced by Asher Blinkoff) from ''[[Hotel Transylvania 2]]'', with the additional voices of [[Selena Gomez]], reprising her role as Mavis, [[Andy Samberg]] as Jonathan, and [[Adam Sandler]] as Dracula. The film is written and directed by veteran director of the ''Hotel Transylvania'' movies, [[Genndy Tartakovsky]], and is shown in theaters alongside ''[[The Emoji Movie]]'', which was released in the United States on July 28, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/01/sony-pictures-animation-the-emoji-movie-spider-man-hotel-transylvania-3-the-star-news-1201889122/|title=Sony Pictures Animation Details Upcoming Slate, Including Julia Roberts\u2019 \u2018Smurfs\u2019 Role|date=January 18, 2017|accessdate=January 20, 2017}}</ref> The film is set in the hotel, as Dennis convinces Dracula to give him a monster-sized puppy named Tinkles, and the hotel learns to cope with it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/01/19/sony-pictures-animation-unveils-spider-man-hotel-transylvania-3-smurfs-and-more/#50b030351b8d|title=Sony Pictures Animation Unveils 'Spider-Man,' 'Hotel Transylvania 3,' 'Smurfs' And More|date=January 19, 2017|accessdate=January 20, 2017}}</ref> The short is a sneak preview of the third film, ''[[Hotel Transylvania 3: Summer Vacation]]'', which was released on July 13, 2018.\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office performance===\n<!-- UPDATE ACCESSDATE IN REF WHEN UPDATING A ROW -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center\" width=99%\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Film\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Release Date\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\" class=sortable | Box Office Grosses\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\" text=\"wrap\" class=unsortable | All Time Ranking\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Budget\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" class=unsortable | References\n|-\n! Domestic\n! International\n! Worldwide\n! class=sortable | [[List of highest-grossing films in Canada and the United States#Not adjusted for inflation|Domestic]]\n! class=sortable | [[List of highest-grossing films#Highest-grossing films|Worldwide]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: left;\"| ''Hotel Transylvania''\n| September 28, 2012\n| $148,313,048\n| $210,062,555\n| $358,375,603\n| 383\n| 373\n| $85 million\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl5801473/|title=Hotel Transylvania|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: left;\"| ''Hotel Transylv