erill]], [[Frank Delgrosso]], H Hawkes\n| con1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 2\n| pen1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] and 1 mark\n| try2 = N Gillies\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = N McCarthy\n| stadium = Carlaw Park\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n===Cambridge v Auckland B===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 19 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Cambridge\n| score = 8-22\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland B (22) V. Cambridge (8)/Fast Interesting Game\n| page = 6\n| publisher = Waikato Independent, Volume XXII, Issue 2587\n| date = 1922-08-22\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/WAIKIN19220822.2.31\n| accessdate = 2020-03-11}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland B\n| try1 = Campbell, Hill\n| con1 = C McMillan\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Wilson 2, E McGregor 2, Stevens, Hanlon\n| con2 = Little, Voysey\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Square, Cambridge\n| attendance =\n| referee = J McIvor\n}}\n\n===Auckland v South Auckland (Northern Union Challenge Cup)===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 2 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 20-21\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =League Challenge Cup/Win by South Auckland/Fast and Exciting Game/Twenty-One Points to Twenty\n| page =9\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LIX, Issue 18186\n| date = 1922-09-04\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19220904.2.122\n| accessdate = 2019-08-29}}</ref>\n| away = South Auckland (Waikato)\n| try1 = [[Craddock Dufty]], [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]], [[Clarrie Polson]],  H Hawkes\n| con1 = [[Craddock Dufty]] 3\n| pen1 = [[Craddock Dufty]]\n| try2 = [[Huatahi 'Brownie' Paki|Brownie Paki]] 2, W Wilson\n| con2 = [[Tonga Mahuta]], C Peckham\n| pen2 = [[Tonga Mahuta]] 4\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance =\n| referee = Bert Gallagher\n}}\n\n===Auckland v New South Wales===\nAuckland played the touring New South Wales team in front of 20,000 spectators at the Auckland Domain but was heavily defeated with Australian legend [[Frank Burge]] running in 5 tries.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 16 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 25-40\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =New South Wales Team\n| page =9\n| publisher =New Zealand Herald, Volume LIX, Issue 18198\n| date = 1922-09-18\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19220918.2.111\n| accessdate = 2019-08-29}}</ref>\n| away = New South Wales\n| try1 = [[Bert Avery]] 2, [[Ivan Littlewood]], [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]] 2\n| con1 = [[Craddock Dufty]], [[Maurice Wetherill]]\n| pen1 = [[Craddock Dufty]] 3\n| try2 = Toohey, Ives, Latta 2, Gray, [[Frank Burge]] 5\n| con2 = Horder 2, [[Frank Burge]] 3\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Auckland Domain\n| attendance = 20000\n| referee = W Murray\n}}\n\n===Auckland Province v New South Wales===\nA few days after the match with New South Wales an Auckland provincial team took on the touring side. The Auckland team was largely made up of Auckland club players but also included William Te Whata and a handful of others from the Waikato. They lost a tight match by 21 points to 20. [[Frank Burge]] was ordered off for disputing Wilson's try late in the match.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland Province\n| score = 20-21\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =League \"Rep\" Match/New South Wales Team/Game Against Province/Win by 21 Points to 20\n| page = 9\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LIX, Issue 18201\n| date = 1922-09-21\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19220921.2.109\n| accessdate = 2020-03-11}}</ref>\n| away = New South Wales\n| try1 = [[Bert Laing]] 2, [[Maurice Wetherill]], Billy Wilson\n| con1 = [[Craddock Dufty]], [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 2\n| pen1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| try2 = H Horder, W Toohey 2, B Grey, [[Frank Burge]]\n| con2 = H Horder, [[Frank Burge]] 2\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Auckland Domain 1\n| attendance = 5500\n| referee = L Bull\n}}\n\n===South Auckland v Auckland (Northern Union Challenge Cup)===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 2 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = South Auckland (Waikato)\n| score = 26-18\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =South Auckland Win/Fast and Open League Play/Auckland Thirteen Defeated/28-16 At the Close\n| page = 6\n| publisher = Waikato Times, Volume 96, Issue 15056\n| date = 1922-10-02\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/WT19221002.2.66\n| accessdate = 2020-03-11}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland\n| try1 = Hemmingway, [[Huatahi 'Brownie' Paki|Brownie Paki]], Bishop, Wilson, Jackson, Guthrie\n| con1 = Hemmingway 3, [[Wilson Hall (rugby league)|Wilson Hall]] 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]], [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]], [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]], Nelson\n| con2 = [[Maurice Wetherill]], [[Clarrie Polson]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Steele Park, Hamilton\n| attendance = 2500\n| referee = A Harlock\n}}\n\n===Bay of Plenty v Auckland===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 7 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Bay of Plenty\n| score = 26-33\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland League Team in Tauranga/Match Against Bay of Plenty\n| page = 3\n| publisher = Bay of Plenty Times, Volume LI, Issue 8109\n| date = 1922-10-07\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/BOPT19221007.2.15\n| accessdate = 2020-03-11}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland\n| try1 = Morrison, G Isles, H Hume, G Gardiner, D Barclay, Ahomiro\n| con1 = G Gardiner 2, Ahomiro\n| pen1 = G Gardiner\n| try2 = [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]] 3, J Johnson, [[Clarrie Polson]], F Wilson, [[Wally Somers]]\n| con2 = Mike Flynn, M Webb 2, [[Clarrie Polson]] 2\n| pen2 = M Webb\n| stadium = Tauranga\n| attendance =\n| referee = A Crane\n}}\n\n==Auckland Representative Matches Played and Scorers==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!No!!Name!!Club Team!!Play!!Tries!!Con!!Pen!!Mark!!Points\n|-\n|1||[[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]||City Rovers||6||5||7||3||1||37\n|-\n|2||[[Craddock Dufty]]||Athletic||4||2||5||4||0||24\n|-\n|2||[[Bert Avery]]||Athletic||8||8||0||0||0||24\n|-\n|4||[[Nelson Bass]]||Marist Old Boys||7||6||1||0||0||20\n|-\n|4||[[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]]||City Rovers||6||6||1||0||0||20\n|-\n|6||[[Clarrie Polson]]||Newton Rangers||8||3||5||0||0||19\n|-\n|7||[[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]]||Newton Rangers||4||6||0||0||0||18\n|-\n|8||[[Maurice Wetherill]]||City Rovers||9||4||2||0||0||16\n|-\n|9||[[Eric Grey]]||Athletic||1||3||0||0||0||9\n|-\n|10||[[Bert Laing]]||Devonport United||5||2||1||0||0||8\n|-\n|11||H Hawkes||City Rovers||8||2||0||0||0||6\n|-\n|11||[[John Lang (New Zealand rugby league)|John Lang]]||Marist Old Boys||4||2||0||0||0||6\n|-\n|11||[[Ivan Littlewood]]||Ponsonby United||5||2||0||0||0||6\n|-\n|11||M Webb||Athletic||1||0||2||1||0||6\n|-\n|15||[[Sam Lowrie]]||Ponsonby United||2||1||1||0||0||5\n|-\n|16||[[Arthur Singe]]||Marist Old Boys||5||0||1||1||0||4\n|-\n|17||[[Frank Delgrosso]]||Ponsonby United||4||1||0||0||0||3\n|-\n|17||[[Wally Somers]]||Newton Rangers||7||1||0||0||0||3\n|-\n|17||[[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]]||City Rovers||3||1||0||0||0||3\n|-\n|17||F Wilson||City Rovers||2||1||0||0||0||3\n|-\n|17||Nelson||Marist Old Boys||1||1||0||0||0||3\n|-\n|17||J Johnson||Devonport United||2||1||0||0||0||3\n|-\n|23||[[Bill Stormont]]||Marist Old Boys||6||0||1||0||0||2\n|-\n|23||Stan Webb||Devonport United||2||0||1||0||0||2\n|-\n|23||[[Thomas McClymont]]||Ponsonby United||3||0||0||1||0||2\n|-\n|23||W Flynn||Athletic||1||0||1||0||0||2\n|-\n|27||F Turner||Marist Old Boys||2||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||[[Charles Woolley (rugby league)|Charles Woolley]]||Fire Brigade||2||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||[[Ernie Herring]]||Fire Brigade||2||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||J McGregor||Athletic||2||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||W Hanlon||Ponsonby United||2||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||Harry Douglas||Devonport United||2||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||P Gallagher||Marist Old Boys||1||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||George Duane||Marist Old Boys||1||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||[[Alf Townsend]]||City Rovers||1||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||Joe Meadows||Ponsonby United||1||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||C Nicholson||Newton Rangers||1||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||G Reid||City Rovers||1||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||Harrison||Devonport United||1||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||Scott||Devonport United||1||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||Mackie||Fire Brigade||1||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||Mitchell||City Rovers||1||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||C Hand||Devonport United||1||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||[[Neville St George]]||Devonport United||1||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|27||[[Jim O'Brien (rugby league)|Jim O'Brien]]||Devonport United||1||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.aucklandleague.co.nz/ Auckland Rugby League Official Site]\n\n[[Category:Auckland Rugby League seasons]]\n[[Category:Rugby league in Auckland]]\n[[Category:Rugby league governing bodies in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Rugby league]]\n", "text_old": "The 1922 [[Auckland Rugby League]] was the 14th in its history. There were 68 teams playing across the various grades. [[City Rovers]] won the first grade championship for the 5th time, with [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby]] winning the Roope Rooster for the 2nd time. [[City Rovers]] also defended the Challenge Shield, warding off efforts from Petone, Tongariro, and Huntly to lift it from them. [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] set a record for points scored in an Auckland club rugby league season with 116 for [[City Rovers]]. He and his brothers [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben]] and [[George Davidson (athlete)|George]] between them scored 186 of City Rover's 339 points which was also a competition record for a team in a single season. City scored a further 19 points in the Roope Rooster competition and 85 points in their 3 Challenge Shield matches for 443 points in all official games.\n\nIt was an incredibly busy year for the Auckland representative team. They played more matches than some club teams had played in earlier seasons with ten matches in total. There was also an Auckland Provincial team match against New South Wales, and one Auckland B fixture with the team making the trip down to Cambridge to play the local side.  [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] also led the representative team in scoring with 37 points.\n\n===Carlaw Park===\nAt a pre-season meeting of the management committee it was discussed that [[Carlaw Park]] needed more \u2018modern equipment\u2019, and it was decided that \u201cthe establishment of more modern methods of dealing with the turf and the purchase of more efficient machinery shall be an early charge on the new season\u2019s funds\u201d.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Management Committee\n| page =3\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LIX, Issue 18042\n| date = 1922-03-17\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19220317.2.16.6\n| accessdate = 2019-08-26}}</ref> Sufficient money was made from gates at club and rep fixtures at Carlaw Park and the Auckland Domain to begin improvements on the ground at the conclusion of the season.\n\n===New Clubs and Name Changes===\nThe [[Auckland Rugby League]] accepted a new club into the fold, named Central Mangere. They entered a team in the 2nd Grade.\n\nThe Maritime club also changed their name to \u2018Athletics\u2019 and in 1926 they were to change their name again to Grafton Athletic. This was not to be confused with [[Grafton Athletic]] who had existed as a team from 1914-1920 under the leadership of [[Karl Ifwersen]] and were now playing under the name of 'Fire Brigade'.\n\n[[Richmond Bulldogs|Richmond Rovers]] applied for entry into the Senior A Grade competition and this was approved. This made the competition an even 8 teams meaning 4 matches per round and no byes. Unlike most previous seasons there were no byes, no defaults, and no postponed matches meaning 56 matches were played in total, easily the most in the competitions history. Richmond would go on to finish 7th with 3 wins and 11 losses.\n\n{{s-start}}\n        {{s-bef|before=[[1921 Auckland Rugby League season|1921]]}}\n        {{s-ttl|title=14th [[Auckland Rugby League]] season\n        |years=1922}}\n        {{s-aft|after=[[1923 Auckland Rugby League season|1923]]}}\n        {{end}}\n\n===George Davidson's Return===\n[[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]] played for Maritime (now named Athletics) in the 1919 season but had missed most of the 1920 and 1921 seasons as he was training for and competing at the Antwerp Olympics where he came 5th in the 200m final. He stated that over those two seasons he had only played for Maritime on two or three occasions as he was seeking a transfer to the [[City Rovers]] where his two brothers [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill]] and [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben]] played. Athletics were denying his request and Davidson appealed to the league who then asked the Athletics club to reconsider his request \"favourably\". He would eventually have his transfer to City approved.\n\n== First Grade Championship ==\n\n=== Final Standings ===\n{|\n|-\n|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=175 |Team\n!width=20 abbr=\"Played\" |Pld\n!width=20 abbr=\"Won\" |W\n!width=20 abbr=\"Drawn\" |D\n!width=20 abbr=\"Lost\" |L\n!width=20 abbr=\"For\" |F\n!width=20 abbr=\"Against\" |A\n!width=20 abbr=\"Points\" |Pts\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[City Rovers|City Rovers]]\n|14||11||0||3||339||157||'''22'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]]\n|14||10||0||4||205||169||'''20'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Marist Saints|Marist Old Boys]]\n|14||9||1||4||258||192||'''19'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[North Shore Albions|Devonport United]]\n|14||7||1||6||223||194||'''15'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Newton Rangers