he Auckland team was largely made up of Auckland club players but also included William Te Whata and a handful of others from the Waikato. They lost a tight match by 21 points to 20. [[Frank Burge]] was ordered off for disputing Wilson's try late in the match.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 20 September\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland Province\n| score = 20-21\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =League \"Rep\" Match/New South Wales Team/Game Against Province/Win by 21 Points to 20\n| page = 9\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LIX, Issue 18201\n| date = 1922-09-21\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19220921.2.109\n| accessdate = 2020-03-11}}</ref>\n| away = New South Wales\n| try1 = [[Bert Laing]] 2, [[Maurice Wetherill]], Billy Wilson\n| con1 = [[Craddock Dufty]], [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 2\n| pen1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| try2 = H Horder, W Toohey 2, B Grey, [[Frank Burge]]\n| con2 = H Horder, [[Frank Burge]] 2\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Auckland Domain 1\n| attendance = 5500\n| referee = L Bull\n}}\n\n===South Auckland v Auckland (Northern Union Challenge Cup)===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 2 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = South Auckland (Waikato)\n| score = 26-18\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =South Auckland Win/Fast and Open League Play/Auckland Thirteen Defeated/28-16 At the Close\n| page = 6\n| publisher = Waikato Times, Volume 96, Issue 15056\n| date = 1922-10-02\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/WT19221002.2.66\n| accessdate = 2020-03-11}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland\n| try1 = Hemmingway, [[Huatahi 'Brownie' Paki|Brownie Paki]], Bishop, Wilson, Jackson, Guthrie\n| con1 = Hemmingway 3, [[Wilson Hall (rugby league)|Wilson Hall]] 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]], [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]], [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]], Nelson\n| con2 = [[Maurice Wetherill]], [[Clarrie Polson]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Steele Park, Hamilton\n| attendance = 2500\n| referee = A Harlock\n}}\n\n===Bay of Plenty v Auckland===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 7 October\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Bay of Plenty\n| score = 26-33\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland League Team in Tauranga/Match Against Bay of Plenty\n| page = 3\n| publisher = Bay of Plenty Times, Volume LI, Issue 8109\n| date = 1922-10-07\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/BOPT19221007.2.15\n| accessdate = 2020-03-11}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland\n| try1 = Morrison, G Isles, H Hume, G Gardiner, D Barclay, Ahomiro\n| con1 = G Gardiner 2, Ahomiro\n| pen1 = G Gardiner\n| try2 = [[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]] 3, J Johnson, [[Clarrie Polson]], F Wilson, [[Wally Somers]]\n| con2 = Mike Flynn, M Webb 2, [[Clarrie Polson]] 2\n| pen2 = M Webb\n| stadium = Tauranga\n| attendance =\n| referee = A Crane\n}}\n\n==Auckland Representative Matches Played and Scorers==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!No!!Name!!Club Team!!Play!!Tries!!Con!!Pen!!Mark!!Points\n|-\n|1||[[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]||City Rovers||6||5||7||3||1||37\n|-\n|2||[[Craddock Dufty]]||Athletic||4||2||5||4||0||24\n|-\n|2||[[Bert Avery]]||Athletic||8||8||0||0||0||24\n|-\n|4||[[Nelson Bass]]||Marist Old Boys||7||6||1||0||0||20\n|-\n|4||[[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]]||City Rovers||6||6||1||0||0||20\n|-\n|6||[[Clarrie Polson]]||Newton Rangers||8||3||5||0||0||19\n|-\n|7||[[Lou Brown (rugby league)|Lou Brown]]||Newton Rangers||4||6||0||0||0||18\n|-\n|8||[[Maurice Wetherill]]||City Rovers||9||4||2||0||0||16\n|-\n|9||[[Eric Grey]]||Athletic||1||3||0||0||0||9\n|-\n|10||[[Bert Laing]]||Devonport United||5||2||1||0||0||8\n|-\n|11||H Hawkes||City Rovers||8||2||0||0||0||6\n|-\n|11||[[John Lang (New Zealand rugby league)|John Lang]]||Marist Old Boys||4||2||0||0||0||6\n|-\n|11||[[Ivan Littlewood]]||Ponsonby United||5||2||0||0||0||6\n|-\n|11||M Webb||Athletic||1||0||2||1||0||6